cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper discusses two on-line computer science citation databases and their differences and similarities. The topics covered in the paper, such as citation analysis and database bias, are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), cryptography (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper focuses on citation databases, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
